"""
Member 2: WLS Volatility Forecasting Pipeline
=================================================================
Source data : optiver_aggregated.csv
              (aggregated from individual_book_train/*.csv)
              Columns: stock_id, time_id, time_bucket,
                       WAP_mean, BidAskSpread_mean, volatility

30-second buckets : CEIL(seconds_in_bucket / 30) → buckets 1–20
                    Each bucket represents exactly 30 seconds of a
                    600-second auction window.


Trader summary
--------------------------------
  "Standard regression (OLS) treats every data point equally, whether
   it came from 10 minutes ago or 10 months ago.  For fast-moving
   markets this is a problem — old market conditions can dilute the
   signal from today's trading.  WLS fixes this by assigning an
   exponentially decaying weight:  w = α^(T − t),  where t is the
   bucket index and T is the last training bucket.  When α is close to
   1 the decay is gentle; when α is small, only very recent buckets
   matter.  We grid-search α on validation QLIKE (the standard
   volatility-forecast loss) so the model automatically learns how
   quickly the market forgets its past.  The result: recent 30-second
   windows count for more, older ones count for less — exactly what a
   trader wants when conditions can shift within a single session."
"""

